description: Returns information about all of your database snapshots in Amazon Lightsail.

parameters.name: pageToken
parameters.description: The token to advance to the next page of results from your request. To get a page token, perform an initial GetRelationalDatabaseSnapshots request. If your results are paginated, the response will return a next page token that you can specify as the page token in a subsequent request.

nested_items.name: relationalDatabaseSnapshots
nested_items.description: An object describing the result of your get relational database snapshots request.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name of the database snapshot.

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the database snapshot.

nested_items.name: supportCode
nested_items.description: The support code for the database snapshot. Include this code in your email to support when you have questions about a database snapshot in Lightsail. This code enables our support team to look up your Lightsail information more easily.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The timestamp when the database snapshot was created.

nested_items.name: availabilityZone
nested_items.description: The Availability Zone. Follows the format us-east-2a (case-sensitive).

nested_items.name: regionName
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services Region name.

nested_items.name: resourceType
nested_items.description: The Lightsail resource type.

nested_items.name: tags
nested_items.description: The tag keys and optional values for the resource. For more information about tags in Lightsail, see the Amazon Lightsail Developer Guide.

nested_items.name: key
nested_items.description: The key of the tag.

nested_items.name: value
nested_items.description: The value of the tag.

nested_items.name: engine
nested_items.description: The software of the database snapshot (for example, MySQL)

nested_items.name: engineVersion
nested_items.description: The database engine version for the database snapshot (for example, 5.7.23).

nested_items.name: sizeInGb
nested_items.description: The size of the disk in GB (for example, 32) for the database snapshot.

nested_items.name: state
nested_items.description: The state of the database snapshot.

nested_items.name: fromRelationalDatabaseName
nested_items.description: The name of the source database from which the database snapshot was created.

nested_items.name: fromRelationalDatabaseArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the database from which the database snapshot was created.

nested_items.name: fromRelationalDatabaseBundleId
nested_items.description: The bundle ID of the database from which the database snapshot was created.

nested_items.name: fromRelationalDatabaseBlueprintId
nested_items.description: The blueprint ID of the database from which the database snapshot was created. A blueprint describes the major engine version of a database.

nested_items.name: nextPageToken
nested_items.description: The token to advance to the next page of results from your request.
